The paper deals with the merging of succinct representations of de Bruijn graphs, which is a topic related to data structures (cs.DS) and graph algorithms (cs.DM). The algorithm proposed in the paper is space efficient, which suggests that it may be relevant to the sub-category of compressed data structures (cs.CC) or external memory algorithms (cs.CE). Finally, the paper also mentions the merging of colored de Bruijn graphs, which is a topic related to database systems (cs.DB).
